1_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000581.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000581-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text of CIL\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>A copy of his will: Greetings, master and father, and farewell, master and father. When I dictated these words to you, I considered you the most miserable person, as you were, when you sent me to this place. I request that you build a monument to me worthy of my youth. I request you to manumit my ward Eutychianus and free him from his bonds, and also my slave Apriles, who is the only survivor of those in my service. Written at Sirmium on the 15th day before the Kalends of April [18 March], during the consulship of L. Calpurnius Piso and P. Salvius Iulianus [175 CE]\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>  \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">10.7457\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 8377 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000352\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000352\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Marino 1974 213-217 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001761\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001761\